{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 23:24:29.755423", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submitted final diagnosis.\n\nSummary:\n- Anomaly detected: Yes\n- Faulty device: web_server_3 (10.200.0.6)\n- Root cause: sender_application_delay\n\nRationale:\n- End-to-end L3 connectivity and DNS resolution are healthy.\n- Multiple independent clients (including loopback on web_server_3) experience HTTP timeouts.\n- A Python HTTP process is listening on :80 but exhibits backlog and fails to service requests, indicating an application-level stall on the sender side rather than network ACL, routing, or firewall issues.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1943, "output_tokens": 116, "total_tokens": 2059, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
